review_blob: served in a can, high abv, but not too heavy. totally enjoyable. it is not a total waste of time if you want to check it out
From the live barrel. Golden red color. Sour and tart but refreshing with hints of vanilla, strawberry that are balanced fantastically too.
Yes, crisp and refreshing with a bitter floral hop profile
Peppery and aromatic flowers. Notes of lavender, chamomile along with a spicy hop profile. This beer is best enjoyed as  fresh as possible.
Fruity notes with belgian yeast, more hoppy than most saisons but definitely not a deal breaker.
beer_name: Three Floyds / De Molen Zes Zes Zes

review_blob: Dammnn, I thought that this has way more hops than expected (in the best possible way). Despite the "double" title, it was not too thick and quite enjoyable.
It really is a plate wrecker, But is this a good thing?  I love most DIPAs, but this is too aggressive and one sided.
High ABV IPA. Honey like color. A bit spicy along with bitter and sweet grapefruit flavors.
beer_name: New Belgium / Alpine Lips of Faith - Super India Pale Ale

review_blob: Had this on draft and it is just as good as expected. Not disappointed at all, hopefully I can find some in bottles too. Light bodied and hoppy citrus flavors, etc...
Lots of grapefruits citrus flavors. Sticky but not cloying at all. Obviously there is rye in it too. Totally legit.
Deep golden body. Big citrus and malt but not an overkill at all. Definitely not amazing, but well done for over 10% abv.
Loads of cherries and is slightly tart.  This beer is totally classic and awesome. I remember it fondly.
Orange color body with big hop flavor and bitter grapefruit finish. On point for sure.
Bloody Mary flavors, especially with the celery.  It is tart and a bit funky.
beer_name: Pegs G.O.O.D. Ich Bin Ein Bloody Berliner

review_blob: UPDATED: MAY 21, 2012
Sweet yellow tropical fruits flavors along with a crisp refreshing sourness. Finishes tart and clean.
beer_name: Cigar City Pilot Series Miami Madness

review_blob: Smells like funky bleu cheese. The aroma is quite powerful but the the beer tastes clean and tart. with some berry sweetness to round it out.
beer_name: Pegs G.O.O.D. Full On Double Rainbow Jelly Donut All The Way Across The Sky

review_blob: Sour, tart along with a dryness that combines in a very refreshing way.  Light citrus flavors as well.
Helles! so good and fresh, reminds me of chilling out in Munich, very tasty brew.
beer_name: Cigar City Hotter Than Helles Lager

review_blob: Every time I have this, I still like it.  Balanced well for all of the big flavors in it.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout (Bourbon Barrel Aged)

review_blob: Nothing too remarkable, but it was totally drinkable for sure.
Perfectly acceptable version of the style. Too bad the Bulls had to lose while I was enjoying it.
Better than most red ales for sure. Just a big, sticky Imperial IPA  or something,
Truly exciting and unique, The  texture and subtleties of this beer are superb, it really is fantastic.
Black and very strong. Burnt malts and booze. Very high abv must be respected when enjoying this beer.
beer_name: The Bruery Black Tuesday Imperial Stout

review_blob: Black malt, roasted barley. A bit sweet and bitter, but still mild. Some floral hop flavors too
Orange, spices coriander.  A little fruit flavors but crisp and refreshing as well.
Tart and sweet, best when fresh too. There is some citrus and spice adding to the flavors too.
Brown, smooth and not as much malt as I expected. Light caramel and sweetness too.
beer_name: Sun King Wee Mac Scottish Ale

review_blob: Mild flavor of roasted malts. Pours out black, just like the name suggests.
Golden orange, bitter with a orange peel finish.  Hops are floral and citrus too.
Heavy malts , floral and malty Bavarian flavors, almost wheat wine or a imperial hefeweiss.
Big sticky hops but no hop bomb at all with sweet golden malt but not cloying. Golden yellow and citrus flavors like grapefruit and oranges.
Dark black and a lot of roasted malt flavor. Smooth and big carbonation as well
Vanilla cake batter flavor, but it is not as hard to drink. The alcohol presence is subtle and makes this beer quite enjoyable.
Big caramel and slightly roasted malts. Drinks smooth and clean, but also deserves to be savored
Earthy, light grass and mild hop presence. Can not remember anything memorable about this beer.
Big brown ale that is drinkable considering the abv. The maple and birch are not overpowering. This beer drinks smoothly and also has some big malt flavors too.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Dogfish Head Life & Limb

review_blob: Thick and caramel bodied with not a overwhelming/ memorable hop profile. Floral/pine hops contribute too,
Dark amber color, caramel hops, slightly nutty and earthy. Very clean and a little spice too,
Golden caramel body. Floral and citrus hops all come together nicely. Overall a good value too. Not too sweet and would love to try it fresh
Floral and bitter with burnt caramel bite. A bit sweet and bitter, with a creamy mouthfeel.
Golden orange form a green can. Burnt candy caramel and tropical fruits. Not too thick but it is sticky, sweet and bitter.
I had this on cask, which made me happy. Golden color, light pine and citrus. Well balanced, finishes dry.
16 oz can, pretty awesome looking. Light malt body with orange, grapefruit and grass notes. Mild hops but they are floral and earthy.  Finishes crisp and dry.
Mild flavors of dark candy fruits probably with some black liquorice or molasses and lightly spiced.  Medium bodied and active carbonation too.
Pours golden orange with big citrus hops and candied fruit flavors. Not a ton of Belgian character, just slightly there underneath all of the the big hops and malt.

review_blob: Banana and clove which is expected in this hefe. Light spices add to the profile as well.
Big and sticky citrus IIPA. Some biscuit along with orange/pine/grapefruit.
